		  <p id="overview">WebVision is an open source web tool that provides a unified rendering engine for psychology and vision study. With WebVision, you can render monocular and binocular content in Virtual Reality, Augmented Reality and Mixed Reality headsets agnostics to the operating system. VR scenes rendered from this application are supported by the majority of modern web browsers, but for more info on which browsers are supported please visit this <span><a target="_blank" href="https://webvr.rocks/">link</a>.</span> </p>
 
			<p>This project was created to assist in the study of lens distortion, pixel structure, refresh rate, lightfield rendering and rendering delay. These are important parameters to study when designing an HMD. </p>
